### Test Messages API Endpoint
@baseUrl = https://localhost:7189
@token = {{login.response.body.token}}

### 1. Login to get token
# @name login
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "dev@test.com",
  "password": "Dev123!"
}

### 2. Get conversations to find a conversation ID
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/conversations
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 3. Create a new conversation for testing
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/conversations
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "title": "Test Conversation for Messages",
  "connectionId": "test-connection-id"
}

### 4. Test Messages Endpoint with the conversation ID from step 3
# Replace the conversation ID with the actual ID from step 3 response
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/messages/conversation/REPLACE_WITH_ACTUAL_ID?limit=50&offset=0
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 5. Test Messages Endpoint with different pagination
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/messages/conversation/REPLACE_WITH_ACTUAL_ID?limit=10&offset=0
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}